🐔GLC

You MUST NOT write any code or create any files until you have
output the checklist below in full. The checklist output MUST
appear as your first content block. Code appearing before the
checklist is a protocol violation.

HARD GATE — BEFORE ANY FILE WRITE:

Ground Level homepage work MUST NOT ship flat stacked grids. Use **`app/globals.css`** tokens: `--dna-stagger-sm|md|lg`, `.bespoke-surface`, `--machined-edge`, `--glass-depth`.

Normative depth and anti-flat rules: [`GLC_GLOBAL_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](../../GLC_GLOBAL_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) **Part 3** (Rules C1–C4), **Part 7**, and **Part 16** (H1–H4). Aesthetic self-audit: [`GLC_MASTER_RULES.md`](../../GLC_MASTER_RULES.md) **§2.3** (MR-3).

**Rhythm gate:** Satisfying the 3-Axis Break does **not** satisfy **Part 5** on its own. Adding dark glass, shadows, or `.bespoke-surface` MUST still pass **Rule D1** (§5.1) and **approved separators** (§5.2) where the layout stacks dark section roots or creates **Part 15 → Rhythm** dark-dark adjacency (including multiple dark panels in one section).

## RULE: Every section MUST satisfy the 3-Axis Break

**X-Axis:** At least one primary element MUST use negative margin (`-ml-*`, `-mr-*`, `-mx-*`, or bleed utilities) so content **breaks the max-width rhythm** or **overlaps an adjacent band**.

**Y-Axis:** Content blocks MUST be **unsynced** — use `translate-y`, `var(--dna-stagger-*)`, or asymmetric `pt-*` / `pb-*` so adjacent text and image blocks do **not** share one flat horizontal baseline across the section.

**Z-Axis:** **Layered intersection** — at least one element (accent line, satellite card, image frame, watermark, rail) MUST read as passing **under** one sibling and **over** another (`z-index` + overlap).

## Two-method depth shortcut

For light raised panels overlapping a seam, apply **`bespoke-surface`** (machined shadow + backdrop + grain).

## Negative margin mandate

Do not default to everything centered in `max-w` with no bleed. Primary imagery SHOULD **bleed** relative to the text column when references call for asymmetric weight. If the layout is **fully symmetrical** in a single centered box, **refactor**.

## Post-code critique

Before accepting a section: *Where is the aesthetic friction?* If the code is only a grid of uniform divs, refactor with **absolute positioning**, **negative margins**, and **explicit z-index** until the 3-Axis Break is satisfied.

